Literally the best math professor ever. He made me turn from a person that absolutely despised math to a person that's planning on minoring in mathematics. He is always willing to help and his teaching technique works extremely well. By far the best math teacher that's ever taught me.

rComments: He is one of the best prof in UTM. His lectures are clear and his tests are really easy(especially final exam). If you practice problems in the textbook, you can get 90+ easily.

Shay was a great prof! Although I didn't do well in his course (YOU MUST PRACTICE TO SUCCEED!), his examples in class were EXACTLY like the questions on tests/problem sets, since he was the course coordinator. Overall funny guy, always tried to make sure we were comfortable before moving on to a new topic. As he says, "practice makes habit!"

Head prof of MAT134 as well as the best prof. Makes the course content easier to learn but if you do not practice, you will not pass. One of the hardest courses in first year. Must do homework every day to do really well on the midterm. This prof gives you the basics of what you need to learn but you need to apply it to very tough practice problems

rComments: Shay is the best Mat134 prof!! Hes very approachable. He tried to be funny in lecture haha. Yes tests were difficult but thats math. Do all the work, problem sets, practice tests and youll actually do well.

Shay is the best math professor for MAT134 tbh.(I went to every MAT134 professor's lecture lol) He explains concepts very well and relates everything (which is really important) The way he transitions from one topic to the next is just flawless. His tests are actually really easy if you're not careless! JUST STUDY

rComments: Shay seems like a very caring professor... Too bad his tests are insanely difficult. On top of that his marking scheme is unfair, you get zero marks short answer questions if you got the wrong answer (even if your steps were correct before the error). No part marks given. Way too difficult of a course for non-math students. TAKE IT IN THE SUMMER!
this is my worst professor ever. He did not even post his notes on the blackboard, portal or in the mailbox. Overall a bad prof. Kick him out please.
WORST PROF EVER. THERE WERE A LOT OF PRESENTATIONS. NOT EVERYBODY IS COMFORTABLE PRESENTING. THEY SHOULD HIRE ANOTHER PROF TO TEACH THIS COURSE. MY GRADE WAS AFFECTED BECAUSE OF PRESENTATIONS.

Nice and approachable. if you're lost with any part he'll help you and explain it at your level. Go to his lectures because it is easily structured and will make you understand the topic better, rather than reading the hard-to-read textbook
One of the nicest and most helpful profs at UTM! I had his courses several times, and even in the summer you want to be there and learn. Hilarious!

He is great in terms of explaining concepts, but the way his tests are formatted is not fair. For the first part of the test he only looks at your final answer and does not give any partial credit even if some of your steps used to reach your final answer were correct.

rComments: One of the best profs out there! Really cares about his students and will go slow if necessary when teaching hard concepts which is a huge plus for any calc course! Tests aren't too bad if you study hard and do the textbook problems!

Shay is an amazing prof. He conveys the information really well and is always willing to make time for his students. If you ever feel confused you should definitely ask him during the breaks or at his office hours. The tests are a bit of a challenge though :(
A real teacher! Fair, approachable, articulate, very attentive. Cristal clear, very detail and lots of examples! The BEST!!!

Man, where do I start? Prof Fuchs is one of the best math profs I've ever had. He is very helpful and nice. His lectures are very clear with plenty of examples. His tests are fair and straightforward. He is an awesome person overall and I would recommend taking 232 with him for sure!

Amazing prof. Knows his stuff inside-out, very helpful, and very clear. If you can attend his lectures, Attend it, even if you aren't in his lecture! Lectures are well structured, easy to follow, and actually teaches you something (unlike the other listen-and-write at the same time profs)

He is a great prof. His lectures are hella boring, but thats probably because I don't like calculus or find it interesting lol. His tests are actually pretty fair as long as you study and do the suggested textbook problems.

rComments: Best prof.

Fuchs is a really good professor (he makes the most adorable jokes!)You can tell he's passionate about math and is a really smart guy.Calculus is challenging, and I've always struggled with math but he made things a little simpler. Problem sets are really easy and the exam was not bad.
Really funny and good at teaching the course is pretty straight forward if you do the past tests and suggested problem then you are well on ur way
great
Awesome prof, very funny and cute ;) Tests can be challenging at times but if you do your work and pay attention, you'll always do well.
His adorableness make his class so much more fun ;) He teaches the class very well. His notes are always good! Best prof at UTM :D

Quizzes and problem sets are free marks pretty much. He makes them really easy and your lowest one doesn't count. Midterm is like past midterms - piece of cake. Final was a bit challenging but not impossible.

Easy course. Prof is CLEAR and notes are neat but material is pointless as his notes don't help with the quizzes. Don't bother going to class unless you really want to learn extra stuff that will just confuse you in the long run. Quizzes are easy, this is not a math course - more like a memorization course,just do the problem sets and you are fine.
makes a lot of mistakes.. clearly does not like teaching... he looks bored
Horrible professor.
Useless professor. Rude!. Do not take him or you'll regret. Choose other professor if you have to take his course.
Great professor! Explained everything extremely well! Make sure to attend class! Notes are extremely helpful!
Wonderful Professor! His tests are really easy if you try the past tests and do all the assigned problems. Many opportunities to improve your mark!
Tests and MT/Final were much more challenging than assignment questions. The latter did not prepare me well for the former.
Excellent prof. His notes are really helpful and he is the best at explaining concepts. The course isn't the easiest, but if you attend all his lectures and do all the work you will do well.
Amazing prof.. calc is hard to begin with so don't expect the course with him to be easy, but he does his best to explain everything as clearly as possible and his tests are pretty fair too !

Definite one of the best profs at utm! He is so clear and concise and his notes are immaculate. He plays math songs to make the course fun/interesting. Of course MAT134 is not an easy course but if you do your homework and read the lecture notes you'll get an A. He's very nice and approachable and is willing to help if you put in the effort.

Fuchs is a really good prof. He writes down everything he talks about and he's a cutie ;) He's nice & approachable. He tries to make math funny & interesting. MAT134 is NOT an easy course. u have to go to lectures, DO HMWK & go over past tests to do well.
Lectures are extremely boring but his notes are excellent and your best source. Do the questions from the textbook, you should do fine :)
Bad on the board but not on the eyes
The easiest prof ever, I did not learn any math and when I needed help he did not explain well. You can skip the lectures and still get A+ in the course.

Overall, Prof. Fuchs is an excellent professor.  The course is difficult at times, but he can explain concepts clearly and is also willing to help anyone who is willing to put in the effort to succeed.
Alright prof. Not remarkable in any way but not bad either.
Best prof at UTM. Played math rap videos. Made math 'recipes'. Overall awesome spirit. Miss this guy!!!

Great Prof. Always willing to help you. Explains questions very clearly. His course might be a little challenging for some people, but if you're willing to put some effort, it's not hard to get a good mark.
Best prof. ever.  He is one of the kindest professors at UTM. Wonderful humble human being.  Awesome to learn from.  Though his tests are freaking gunning for you lol...

This prof is the best I've ever had. He explains everything and tries to give you good examples and techniques that will help. In 102, the textbook was terrible, but it didn't matter, cause as long as you copied the notes, you'd do pretty well. TAKE HIS CLASS, YOU WON'T REGRET IT!

Excellent professor.  I'm back for my second degree and he's by far one of the best professors I've ever had.
Simply amazing! =) Fuchs is the best prof I ever had :)

Great Prof :)
